Package: CSEM
Type: Estimation and utilities for conditional standard error of measurement for scores
Title: Conditional Standard Error of Measurement Methods for Test Scores
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Cesar", "Merino-Soto",
      email = "sikayax@yahoo.com.ar",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Provides functions to compute and compare conditional standard
    errors of measurement (CSEM) across score distributions using multiple
    statistical approaches from test classical theory. Includes methods for
    smoothing, CSEM using bootstrapping, standardized CSEM, CSEM for scale
    score, check propierties of two-halves scores, and comparison with global
    standard errors of measurement derived from reliability coefficients. The
    package supports graphical visualization of CSEM curves and relative 
    precision across observed score ranges.
URL: https://github.com/cmerinos/CSEM
BugReports: https://github.com/cmerino/CSEM/issues
